<taxonomicName id="1B59F7CD7AAD71360252334007326463" LSID="4E453231-C812-5686-AC11-BC30439E9BDB" authority="(Giesecke ex Lindenb.) Dumort., Recueil Observ. Jungerm.: 24, 1835." authorityName="(Giesecke ex Lindenb.) Dumort., Recueil Observ. Jungerm.: 24, 1835." authorityYear="1835" class="Hepaticae" family="Gymnomitriaceae" genus="Marsupella" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Marsupella sphacelata" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="sphacelata">Marsupella sphacelata (Giesecke ex Lindenb.) Dumort., Recueil Observ. Jungerm.: 24, 1835.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EE64E95A56E58ADE2010ADDCE8A653D" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9490C514C7FF89BBE67C92A9937B9A8A" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B120AB148C9127AA92823B631A17CA2" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">
The taxon was recorded for North Korea (Gangwon-do, Hamgyeongnam-do, cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="06C3FD37D5EFE22051ED5D3A0540FC9F" author="Kim, YH" journalOrPublisher="Publishing House of Science on Encyclopodia, Pyongyang" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" refId="B9" refString="Kim, YH, Hwang, HJ, 1991. Korean Spore Plant 8 (Hepaticae). Publishing House of Science on Encyclopodia, Pyongyang" title="Korean Spore Plant 8 (Hepaticae)." year="1991">Kim and Hwang 1991</bibRefCitation>
), but was not found in specimens examined. We suggest that all reports regarding the occurrence of this species in Korea and adjacent regions are erroneous and probably belong to 
<taxonomicName id="643DACB45F22639D6ECA67D6E1A422BF" family="Gymnomitriaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. apertifolia" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" rank="species" species="apertifolia">
<emphasis id="EE74288AB10F49E1787ACBAEAB88FB81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">M. apertifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to which the species are similar in coloration and rounded leaf lobes, but differ in leaf margin characteristics, leaf sinus deepness, and stem cross section features, all of which are included in the identification key. In general, 
<taxonomicName id="8EC160F9C889F3FAFC89870173995B2D" family="Gymnomitriaceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sphacelata" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" rank="species" species="sphacelata">
<emphasis id="C883BBD08375F0A95EA670D7D257ECD1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">M. sphacelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rarity in East Asia and probably absent southward of 53Â°N (southern part of Kamchatka Peninsula). The records for Honshu Island in Japan are doubtful due to reported red pigmentation (
<bibRefCitation id="C9DF01F1D0C0D93B47CBE1D988BE8256" author="Kitagawa, N" journalOrPublisher="The Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" pagination="76 - 118" refId="B10" refString="Kitagawa, N, 1963. A revision of the family Marsupellaceae of Japan. The Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 26: 76 - 118" title="A revision of the family Marsupellaceae of Japan." volume="26" year="1963">Kitagawa 1963</bibRefCitation>
) which is not known for this species from other parts of its range (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="B29A911B2981F074BDA0D6B9862D9207" author="Schuster, RM" journalOrPublisher="Columbia University Press, New York and London" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" refId="B17" refString="Schuster, RM, 1974. The Hepaticae and Anthocerotae of North America East of the Hundredth Meridian. Vol. 3. Columbia University Press, New York and London" title="The Hepaticae and Anthocerotae of North America East of the Hundredth Meridian. Vol. 3." year="1974">Schuster 1974</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
